[Conda psi4 bad shared object names][4]

 Sometimes psi4 (installed from conda) looks for .so's named differently th=
an what exists on the machine: 

psi4: error while loading shared libraries: libhdf5.so.10: cannot open shar=
ed object file: No such file or directory 

I can fix this with a symbolic link, but that is annoying, and I don't know=
 enough to know if this will ever cause problems.  Any ideas?
